<para>       <emphasis emphasis-type="bold">READING</emphasis>     </para>
<para>       <emphasis emphasis-type="bold">SECTION DIRECTIONS</emphasis>
   </para>
<para></para>
<para>In this section of the test, you will read three passages. You will
be tested on your ability to understand them by answering several questions
on each passage.</para>
<para></para>
<para>While you read, you may take notes. You can then use your notes when
answering questions.</para>
<para></para>
<para>Most questions are worth one point. Questions that are worth more than
one point have a special note telling you how many total points they are worth.</para>
<para></para>
<para>You will have 60 minutes to read the three passages and answer all questions.
Some of the passages include a word or phrase that is in blue color. Click
on such word or phrase to see a definition or explanation.</para>
<para></para>
<para>When you are ready to move to the next question, click on <emphasis
emphasis-type="bold">Next</emphasis>. In this section, it is possible to skip
questions and then return to the later, as long as there is time remaining.
When you want to return to previous questions that you have skipped, click
on <emphasis emphasis-type="bold">Back</emphasis>.</para>
<para></para>
<para>Clicking on <emphasis emphasis-type="bold">Review</emphasis> in this
section will take you to a review screen which shows the questions you have
answered and the questions you have not answered. You are able to go directly
to a new question in this section from the review screen.</para>
<para></para>
<para>When you are ready to begin the Reading section, click on <emphasis
emphasis-type="bold">Next</emphasis>.</para>
</document>
</gradItems>
